# Shell and Tool Config

## Shell init ownership

Tool init lives in **zsh/bash packages**, not tool packages:

| Tool | Init file | Config files |
|------|-----------|--------------|
| Starship | `zsh/starship.zsh`, `bash/starship.sh` | `starship/starship.toml`, `starship.light.toml` |
| Bat | `bat/.config/zsh/bat.zsh`, `bat/.config/bash/bat.sh` | (aliases only) |

- Zsh `.zshrc` sources `starship.zsh` unconditionally
- Bash `bashrc` sources `starship.sh` from `CONFIG_DIR`
- Bat uses conditional source: `[[ -f "$ZDOTDIR/bat.zsh" ]] && source ...`

Never use conditional-only sourcing for required prompts without a fallback.

## Starship light/dark

- Edit `starship/.config/starship.toml`, then run `./starship/sync_light_config.sh`
- Commit both `starship.toml` and `starship.light.toml`
- Detection: `STARSHIP_APPEARANCE`, WezTerm (always dark), macOS `AppleInterfaceStyle`, `COLORFGBG`, fallback dark
- Details: [starship/README.md](../../starship/README.md)

## Bat

- Aliases only when `bat` binary is present
- `setup_bat()` offers to comment out conflicting `cat` aliases in local RC files
